  "description": [
    "18 SEEKS TO PREVENT ACTS BY JUVENILES Child Labor Conference Opposes Stage Life for Children State laws Cited BARRED IN PENNSYLVANIA Conferees Discuss Principal Prob lems to Be Overcome How children are prevented from a wearing in professional theatricals In the state of Pennsylvania but can not be so prohibited in New York state was outlined before the twen tieth anniversary conference on child labor today at the Washington Hotel The Butterfly Kiddies and even other productions left Pennsylvania for other backward nearby states following court action and official warnings Dr Royal Meeker secre tary of labor and Industry of Penn sylvania explained Admitting that there were con flicting state court decisions as to whether the state law was operative against children on the stage Dr Sleeker said the administration was progressing under the decision which prohibited children on the stage The principal problems however Dr Meeker said in enforcement of child labor laws were to get the proper personnel for administration and sufficient money Assistant Industrial Commissioner Orennan of theNew York state de partment of labor admitted that the child labor laws of that state did not prohibit children on the stage Three things were needed he said in"
